<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871022-0121 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Trinova Corp.</HL><DD> 10/22/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TNVBOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><TEXT>   TRINOVA CORP., Maumee, Ohio, said it signed an underwriting agreement for the previously announced public offering in the Eurodollar markets of $100 million of convertible subordinated debentures with a 6% annual coupon, due Oct. 15, 2002. Trinova makes machinery components. The offering is being made by an international group led by Salomon Brothers International Ltd., Morgan Stanley International and Bear Stearns International Ltd. </TEXT></DOC>